15/05/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica kicks off a two-day working visit to Germany on Monday (15 May).
He will be meeting with counterpart Angela Merkel, Foreign Minister Frank-Walter Steinmeier, members of parliament and business leaders in Berlin and Duesseldorf.
Strengthening bilateral economic ties and the Euro-Atlantic integration aspirations of Serbia-Montenegro are the likely focus of discussions.
(Beta, Danas - 15/05/06;
RTS - 14/05/06)
